<subSubSection id="A6D56B14934A2F1BAB7381E9D8D3D8C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6E30C5D2A5D5EFD6D8888889816B4F36" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F167C1E14ABC5D4D06CED35163F79F5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
Known distribution: Antilles, Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Mexico, Nicaragua, Panama, United States of America and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation id="DAC2E05D485E76D632CD0244395BFCC8" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
). Fig. 19.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ECDF32C365F2988CA754C6D54F1A8085" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="1D6FB7B732C3CCA7948FC59CF69223ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19E7B4DF62A9571DDB9283967BEF6C60" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Occurs as terrestrial or rupestrial in montane wet and seasonal forests.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B297AD174B7B8A2135A6BFBF9CAA4C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="2D1640119912A5F30C413BAF9E86C1E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F23002D0B09B07C56E35F3F385C4E8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This is a very common species in Central America, also occurring in northern South America. It can be recognized by peltate indusia and entire pinnae or lobes (
<bibRefCitation id="12D68BE154599D4B937710741D17FCB1" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
). The closest species is 
<taxonomicName id="9D3B37592EA8A75E8EA6407CC290B815" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Tectariaceae" genus="Tectaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tectaria incisa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incisa">Tectaria incisa</taxonomicName>
Cav., from which 
<taxonomicName id="615E1EC7B365AD6F5A759DAEBB8BE6A2" genus="T." lsidName="T. heracleifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" rank="species" species="heracleifolia">T. heracleifolia</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by peltate indusia, cordiform bases of pinnae and apical segment and smaller number of pinnae (
<bibRefCitation id="1B96B608907EA8CE124677F1ADB2930B" author="Moran, R. C." editor="Davidse, G." journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Ciudad de Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora Mesoamericana" year="1995">Moran 1995b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
